<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,546,717]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,546,572]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Comments:</emphasis>
Only one individual was collected, presenting: (1) the ventral portion of all tibiae and femora black, (2) wings not so long as twice of the length of the femur III, with numerous black punctuations, very conspicuous just below Sc+R, (3) rhomboid vertex, longer than wide, with whitish apex, (4) fastigium of the vertex entirely black, (5) oval mirror, with a straight anterior margin while the other areas are convex.
</paragraph>
